==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Regent diamond
<hw>Re"gent di"a*mond</hw>. <def>A famous diamond of fine quality, which
weighs about 137 carats and is among the state jewels of France. It is
so called from the Duke of Orleans, Regent of France, to whom it was
sold in 1717 by Pitt the English Governor of Madras (whence also called
the <altname>Pitt diamond</altname>), who bought it of an Indian
merchant in 1701.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Regentess</ent>⟦br⟧
